<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,1282]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1184,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">Comment:</emphasis>
This species was previously synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Snelling" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[876,1016,1184,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons">
<emphasis box="[876,895,1185,1211]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[910,1016,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">flavifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Snelling, R. R." box="[1061,1240,1184,1211]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref23559" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling (1984)</bibRefCitation>
. However, it was considered valid by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[377,600,1220,1247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[459,508,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. The study of the primary 
<typeStatus box="[895,954,1221,1247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="236">types</typeStatus>
of both species allows confirming they are conspecific.
</paragraph>
